    <div>
        <h2>Anne Kwaspen</h2>
        <p>
            Anne Kwaspen, former Director of the Belgian Fashion Museum ‘Modemuseum Hasselt’ and Conservator of the Egyptian textile collection 
            of the Phoebus Foundation, Antwerp, is specialized in costume history, archaeological Egyptian textiles, and technical analyses of 
            textile structures. She is a member of the BYU Egypt Excavation Team since 2018. Currently, as Marie Sklodowska-Curie fellow at Centre 
            of Textile Research of the University of Copenhagen, she studies the different styles of clothing worn in Egypt.
        </p>
    </div>
